      <h1>Perplexity vs ChatGPT: Which AI Search Tool Is Better in 2026?</h1>
      <p class="meta">Updated June 2, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <p class="lead">
      In 2026, AI-powered search is exploding. <strong>Perplexity</strong> built its entire product around search with inline citations, while <strong>ChatGPT</strong> added web browsing as a feature on top of its general-purpose AI capabilities. Both tools can answer questions with real-time information, but they approach the problem from completely different directions. After testing both extensively for research accuracy, writing quality, fact-checking reliability, and everyday knowledge work across dozens of real-world scenarios, here is the detailed comparison you need to decide which one fits your workflow best.
    </p>

    <div class="tldr">
      <h2>TL;DR</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Perplexity</strong> wins on search accuracy, real-time citations, and deep research. Best for students, journalists, analysts, and anyone who needs verifiable sources.</li>
        <li><strong>ChatGPT</strong> wins on writing, coding, image generation, and multimodal features. Best for content creators, developers, and general-purpose AI users.</li>
        <li><strong>Pricing:</strong> Both cost $20/month for the Pro tier; value depends on whether your work is research-heavy or creation-heavy.</li>
        <li><strong>Verdict:</strong> Use Perplexity for finding and verifying information. Use ChatGPT for creating and acting on information. Many pros run both.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

